The paper also uses Gaussian-process models and Bayesian methods, which are common in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with estimation and approximation techniques, which are common in information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE).
